observations.recommendation:
We recommended that the LDRRM Council, through the LDRRM Officer:

Update the LDRRMF Investment Plan to include the specific, necessary and appropriate PPAs needed to address the COVID-19 situation affecting the LGU and itemize therein the PPAs to ensure that utilization of the fund is covered with appropriate authority;

Convene and amend Resolution No. 02-03-2020 to correct the errors in its contents to support the updated LDRRMFIP;

Present the list of projects and activities charged to the unexpended LDRRMF of previous years under a separate caption in the succeeding year’s LDRRMFIP and incorporate the same in the Annual Investment Plan.

We recommended that the Bookkeeper and the Municipal Accountant:
record in the appropriate expense or asset accounts any amount utilized or paid from the funds received from NGAs, and;
record a reduction (debit) in the Due to NGAs account and the corresponding revenue account only when the purpose of the project and program is completed and the Fund Utilization Reports/Liquidation Report is submitted to the source agency.

We recommended that the LDRRM Council, through the LDRRM Officer:
Update the LDRRMF Investment Plan to include the specific, necessary and appropriate PPAs needed to address the COVID-19 situation affecting the LGU and itemize therein the PPAs to ensure that utilization of the fund is covered with appropriate authority;
Convene and amend Resolution No. 02-03-2020 to correct the errors in its contents to support the updated LDRRMFIP;
Present the list of projects and activities charged to the unexpended LDRRMF of previous years under a separate caption in the succeeding year’s LDRRMFIP and incorporate the same in the Annual Investment Plan.
